Definition: [κοσμοκράτωρ] from {{g2889}} and {{g2902}}; a world-ruler, an epithet of Satan

[κόσμος] probably from the base of {{g2865}}; orderly arrangement, i.e. decoration; by implication, the world (in a wide or narrow sense, including its inhabitants, literally or figuratively (morally))
[κορέννυμι] a primary verb; to cram, i.e. glut or sate
[Κορίνθιος] from {{g2882}}; a Corinthian, i.e. inhabitant of Corinth
[Κόρινθος] of uncertain derivation; Corinthus, a city of Greece
[Κορνήλιος] of Latin origin; Cornelius, a Roman
[κόρος] of Hebrew origin ({{h3734}}); a cor, i.e. a specific measure
[κοσμέω] from {{g2889}}; to put in proper order, i.e. decorate (literally or figuratively); specially, to snuff (a wick)
[κοσμικός] from {{g2889}} (in its secondary sense); terrene ("cosmic"), literally (mundane) or figuratively (corrupt)
[κόσμιος] from {{g2889}} (in its primary sense); orderly, i.e. decorous
[κλάσμα] from {{g2806}}; a piece (bit)
[Κλαύδη] of uncertain derivation; Claude, an island near Crete
[Κλαυδία] feminine of {{g2804}}; Claudia, a Christian woman
[Κλαύδιος] of Latin origin; Claudius, the name of two Romans
[κλαυθμός] from {{g2799}}; lamentation
[κλάω] a primary verb; to break (specially, of bread)
[κλείς] from {{g2808}}; a key (as shutting a lock), literally or figuratively
[κλείω] a primary verb; to close (literally or figuratively)
[κλέμμα] from {{g2813}}; stealing (properly, the thing stolen, but used of the act)
[κόπτω] a primary verb; to "chop"; specially, to beat the breast in grief Compare the base of {{g5114}}.
[κοπρία] from κόπρος (ordure; perhaps akin to {{g2875}}); manure
[κοράσιον] neuter of a presumed derivative of κόρη (a maiden); a (little) girl
[κόραξ] perhaps from {{g2880}}; a crow (from its voracity)
[κοπή] from {{g2875}}; cutting, i.e. carnage
[κοπετός] from {{g2875}}; mourning (properly, by beating the breast)
[κόπος] from {{g2875}}; a cut, i.e. (by analogy) toil (as reducing the strength), literally or figuratively; by implication, pains
[κοπιάω] from a derivative of {{g2873}}; to feel fatigue; by implication, to work hard
[Κορέ] of Hebrew origin ({{h7141}}); Core (i.e. Korach), an Israelite

[κορβᾶν]   and κορβανᾶςof Hebrew and Chaldee origin respectively ({{h7133}}); a votive offering and the offering; a consecrated present (to the Temple fund); by extension (the latter term) the Treasury itself, i.e. the room where the contribution boxes stood
[κομψότερον] neuter comparative of a derivative of the base of 2865 (meaning, properly, well dressed, i.e. nice); figuratively, convalescent
[κονιάω] from κονία (dust; by analogy, lime); to whitewash
[κόμη] apparently from the same as {{g2865}}; the hair of the head (locks, as ornamental, and thus differing from {{g2359}}; which properly denotes merely the scalp)
[κομίζω] from a primary κομέω (to tend, i.e. take care of); properly, to provide for, i.e. (by implication) to carry off (as if from harm; genitive case obtain)
[κολωνία] of Latin origin; a Roman "colony" for veterans
[κομάω] from {{g2864}}; to wear tresses of hair
[κολυμβάω] from κόλυμβος (a diver); to plunge into water
[κολυμβήθρα] from {{g2860}}; a diving-place, i.e. pond for bathing (or swimming)
[κραταιός] from {{g2904}}; powerful
[κονιορτός] from the base of {{g2867}} and ornumi (to "rouse"); pulverulence (as blown about)
[κοπάζω] from {{g2873}}; to tire, i.e. (figuratively) to relax
[κολλάω] from κόλλα ("glue"); to glue, i.e. (passively or reflexively) to stick (figuratively)
[κολαφίζω] from a derivative of the base of {{g2849}}; to rap with the fist
[κόλασις] from {{g2849}}; penal infliction
[κολακεία] from a derivative of κόλαξ (a fawner); flattery
[Κολοσσαί] apparently feminine plural of kolossos ("colossal"); Colossæ, a place in Asia Minor
[κολοβόω] from a derivative of the base of {{g2849}}; to dock, i.e. (figuratively) abridge
[κολλυβιστής] from a presumed derivative of κόλλυβος (a small coin; probably akin to {{g2854}}); a coin-dealer
[κολλούριον] neuter of a presumed derivative of κολλύρα (a cake; prob akin to the base of {{g2853}}); properly, a poultice (as made of or in the form of crackers), i.e. (by analogy) a plaster
[κόλπος] apparently a primary word; the bosom; by analogy, a bay
[Κολοσσαεύς] from {{g2857}}; a Colossæan, (i.e. inhabitant of Colossæ
[κόκκος] apparently a primary word; a kernel of seed
[κολάζω] from κόλος (dwarf); properly, to curtail, i.e. (figuratively) to chastise (or reserve for infliction)
[κοινωνός] from {{g2839}}; a sharer, i.e. associate
[κοίτη] from {{g2749}}; a couch; by extension, cohabitation; by implication, the male sperm
[κοιτών] from {{g2845}}; a bedroom
[κόκκινος] from {{g2848}} (from the kernel-shape of the insect); crimson-colored
[κοινόω] from {{g2839}}; to make (or consider) profane (ceremonially)
[κοινωνέω] from {{g2844}}; to share with others (objectively or subjectively)
[κοινωνία] from {{g2844}}; partnership, i.e. (literally) participation, or (social) intercourse, or (pecuniary) benefaction
[κοινωνικός] from {{g2844}}; communicative, i.e. (pecuniarily) liberal
[κοινός] probably from {{g4862}}; common, i.e. (literally) shared by all or several, or (ceremonially) profane
[κοίμησις] from {{g2837}}; sleeping, i.e. (by implication) repose
[κλυδωνίζομαι] middle voice from {{g2830}}; to surge, i.e. (figuratively) to fluctuate
[κλύδων] from κλύζω (to billow or dash over); a surge of the sea (literally or figuratively)
[κνήθω] from a primary κνάω (to scrape); to scratch, i.e. (by implication) to tickle
[Κλωπᾶς] of Chaldee origin (corresponding to {{h256}}); Clopas, an Israelite
[κοδράντης] of Latin origin; a quadrans, i.e. the fourth part of an as
[Κνίδος] probably of foreign origin; Cnidus, a place in Asia Minor
[κοιμάω] from {{g2749}}; to put to sleep, i.e. (passively or reflexively) to slumber; figuratively, to decease
[κοιλία] from κοῖλος ("hollow"); a cavity, i.e. (especially) the abdomen; by implication, the matrix; figuratively, the heart
[κλισία] from a derivative of {{g2827}}; properly, reclination, i.e. (concretely and specially), a party at a meal
[κλοπή] from {{g2813}}; stealing
[κλητός] from the same as {{g2821}}; invited, i.e. appointed, or (specially), a saint
[κλίβανος] of uncertain derivation; an earthen pot used for baking in
[κληρόω] from {{g2819}}; to allot, i.e. (figuratively) to assign (a privilege)
[κλῆσις] from a shorter form of {{g2564}}; an invitation (figuratively)
[κλινίδιον] neuter of a presumed derivative of {{g2825}}; a pallet or little couch
[κλίνω] a primary verb; to slant or slope, i.e. incline or recline (literally or figuratively)
[κλίμα] from {{g2827}}; a slope, i.e. (specially) a "clime" or tract of country
[κλίνη] from {{g2827}}; a couch (for sleep, sickness, sitting or eating)
[κράσπεδον] of uncertain derivation; a margin, i.e. (specially), a fringe or tassel
[κρανίον] diminutive of a derivative of the base of {{g2768}}; a skull ("cranium")
[κραιπάλη] probably from the same as {{g726}}; properly, a headache (as a seizure of pain) from drunkenness, i.e. (by implication) a debauch (by analogy, a glut)
[κράζω] a primary verb; properly, to "croak" (as a raven) or scream, i.e. (genitive case) to call aloud (shriek, exclaim, intreat)
[κράββατος] probably of foreign origin; a mattress
[κόφινος] of uncertain derivation; a (small) basket
[κουφίζω] from κοῦφος (light in weight); to unload
[κουστωδία] of Latin origin; "custody", i.e. a Roman sentry
[κοῦμι] of Chaldee origin ({{h6966}}); cumi (i.e. rise!)
[Κούαρτος] of Latin origin (fourth); Quartus, a Christian
[κληρονομία] from {{g2818}}; heirship, i.e. (concretely) a patrimony or (genitive case) a possession
[κληρονομέω] from {{g2818}}; to be an heir to (literally or figuratively)
[Κλήμης] of Latin origin; merciful; Clemes (i.e. Clemens), a Christian
[κλῆμα] from {{g2806}}; a limb or shoot (as if broken off)
[κλέπτω] a primary verb; to filch
[κλέπτης] from {{g2813}}; a stealer (literally or figuratively) Compare {{g3027}}.
[κλέος] from a shorter form of {{g2564}}; renown (as if being called)
[Κλεόπας] probably contracted from Κλεόπατρος (compound of {{g2811}} and {{g3962}}); Cleopas, a Christian

[κλῆρος] probably from {{g2806}} (through the idea of using bits of wood, etc., for the purpose; a die (for drawing chances); by implication, a portion (as if so secured); by extension, an acquisition (especially a patrimony, figuratively)

[κληρονόμος] from {{g2819}} and the base of {{g3551}} (in its original sense of partitioning, i.e. (reflexively) getting by apportionment); a sharer by lot, i.e. inheritor (literally or figuratively); by implication, a possessor
